div1.p:
I lost the things mentioned in the indictment, on the ninth of this month;
Sarah Pettit
lives with me in the same room; I got them again the same morning in Catherine-wheel-alley, I overtook the prisoner in the street, with the property in her apron, I never saw her before that morning, and I found Mrs. Pettit's property also upon her: she gave no account of herself, I called no assistance, I secured her myself, and brought her back again with the property on her, I charged the constable with her.
